    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>St. Thomas</placeName>
                <date>30 Dec 1849</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My Dr Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">I have not had this pleasure for some time<lb/> not having any thing
                of great importance to communicate<lb/> I recd your introductory letter for
                    <persName>Rabbi Cohen</persName> &amp; paid him<lb/> attention I collected $154
                for him he left for <placeName>Curacao</placeName> 15<lb/> days ago.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">It was with much <del>regret</del> pain I read your letter of
                    <date>29 Oct</date><lb/> stating that in consequence of the differences with
                yourself &amp;<lb/> congregation it was not unlikely that you would give up<lb/>
                your situation as minister. I hope that your anticipations<lb/> will not be realized
                &amp; that you may for many years continue<lb/> your duties. I regret to join you in
                opinion that the greater<lb/> portion of our people lack in respect to their
                ministers &amp;<lb/> require them to be the tail instead of heads of
                Congregations,<lb/> this feeling &amp; the <sic>apparant</sic> non-desire for
                religious Instruction,<lb/> added to the disinclination of contributing a few
                dollars<lb/> prevents our having a minister. I confess that I am tired of<lb/>
                exertion in this cause my return has been, &amp; is, <hi rend="underline"
                    >Enemies</hi> the<lb/> only chance that a portion of our young people have
                of<lb/> religious instruction is what my very feeble abilities can<lb/> impart to
                them thro' the Sunday School, &amp; even this altho'<lb/> gratuitous I can with
                difficulty keep together, I am<lb/> however determined to keep it up so long as the
                Almighty<lb/> spares me health; even the leaches have fallen off &amp; my Wife<lb/>
                &amp; self are the only ones who keep it on, God may in his<lb/> mercy bring us a
                change.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Enclosed I forward you a pact of Hymns used in<lb/> the Sunday
                School which I wish you to have printed in<lb/> pamphlets of equal sized leaves
                neatly done. I require Two<lb/> hundred with covers,The following Hymns composed by
                Mr.</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p><persName>Mr Carillon</persName> I wish his name attached to</p>
            <p>N 1 Introductory Hymn</p>
            <p>  2 Halel</p>
            <p>  3 ditto    with the written alterations</p>
            <p>  4 ditto</p>
            <p>  6 choir No1</p>
            <p>  7 do         2 with the word “both” inscribed in the<lb/> second verse 1 Line as
                noted</p>
            <p>  8 En Kelihener</p>
            <p>  9 Forward to Jerusalem</p>
            <p> the following after</p>
            <p>O “God to thee my voice I raise; (by a Young Lady at
                <placeName>Richmond</placeName>.</p>
            <p>Paraphrase of the Hebrew Creed,</p>
            <p rend="align(right)">from the Jewish Chronicle</p>
            <p><date>Sabbath-Eve</date> Hymn</p>
            <p>Costly—Conclusive Hymn from <persName>Revd DeSola's</persName><lb/> prayer Book.</p>
            <p>I leave the arrangement of the Frontspiece to you.<lb/> I would like it to run
                thus</p>
            <p>“Hymns” composed by the <persName>Revd B C Carillon</persName> for the use<lb/> of
                the <placeName>St Thomas</placeName> Israelite Sunday School, as well as<lb/> others
                selected for the same purpose by <persName role="author">A Wolff</persName><lb/>
                Founder &amp; Instructor</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The <hi rend="underline">School opened in</hi> the month of
                    <date>April 1842</date><lb/> Let me ask you to improve the above if you think
                it<lb/> necessary. I require 2 dozen of <persName><sic>Picke's</sic></persName>
                Catechisms for<lb/> infants please forward them with as little delay as<lb/>
                possible</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I suppose that <persName>Mr Nathan</persName> Must be now in<lb/>
                <placeName>New Orleans</placeName> I hear that he is to be minister there</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My wife joins with best regards, &amp; I am</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Yours Truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">A. Wolff</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd. Mr. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
